16:08.482 --> 16:11.250
You move and I'll shoot you.

16:12.921 --> 16:14.252
(WHIMPERS)

16:26.829 --> 16:29.012
These stitches won't hold.

16:29.013 --> 16:31.515
- This thread ain't the right kind of...
- I'll be fine.

16:31.516 --> 16:33.067
You need a doctor.

16:34.069 --> 16:35.936
I'll send Isaac for a doctor.

16:50.419 --> 16:51.584
(SNIFFLES)

16:52.254 --> 16:54.387
(STRAINING) Camp Douglas has a doctor.

16:56.258 --> 16:58.508
You won't make it half way.

16:58.509 --> 16:59.825
He won't let you.

17:00.662 --> 17:02.128
(HEAVY BREATHING)

17:02.397 --> 17:03.896
He will hang.

17:04.799 --> 17:06.165
Then why go?

17:07.769 --> 17:08.968
End it here.

17:23.518 --> 17:25.217
(GRUNTG)

17:40.367 --> 17:43.502
THE SWEDE: Tell me where...
Where are we headed, huh?

17:45.106 --> 17:47.089
If you wanted to kill
me you would have...

17:47.090 --> 17:48.941
You would have done
it down in the creek.

17:50.411 --> 17:52.929
Uh, perhaps a slow death, eh?

17:52.930 --> 17:54.213
Torture.

17:55.482 --> 17:57.916
Mmm, the leg in that condition...

17:58.652 --> 18:03.387
No man tortures his enemy if he must
torture himself in the process.

18:05.759 --> 18:08.176
Camp Douglas, huh?

18:08.177 --> 18:11.179
Some 60 miles west of Gobbler's Knob,

18:11.180 --> 18:16.835
with jurisdiction over all crimes
committed in the Utah Territory.

18:17.671 --> 18:20.088
You want this to end in the way

18:20.089 --> 18:24.308
you believe it should have ended a long
time ago upon that trestle bridge.

18:26.578 --> 18:31.715
Uh, Heavenly Father has
spared my neck twice now.

18:32.451 --> 18:35.019
He can manage a third, hmm?

18:42.394 --> 18:45.145
THE SWEDE: My friend took a
ball to the leg during the war.

18:45.146 --> 18:49.733
Same place as you. You would
not believe how he suffered.

18:50.302 --> 18:51.719
CULLEN: I don't believe
you had a friend.

18:51.720 --> 18:55.723
THE SWEDE: Uh, uh, Confederate
soldiers took us captive,

18:55.724 --> 18:58.125
forced us to ride two days,

18:58.126 --> 19:00.544
about the same distance
we are traveling, yeah?

19:01.613 --> 19:05.332
By the time we arrived at
the Georgia state line,

19:05.333 --> 19:07.350
gangrene had set in.

19:08.654 --> 19:11.838
A river of shit ran through
the center of Andersonville,

19:11.839 --> 19:17.460
and I tell you the stench of
Goodwin's wound overpowered it.

19:17.862 --> 19:19.128
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

19:19.431 --> 19:21.348
The rot did not take his leg.

19:21.349 --> 19:24.834
Uh, the rebels did. And
with it, his dignity.

19:26.405 --> 19:30.674
Imagine saving a man's life
only to watch his slow death.

19:31.476 --> 19:34.877
What breed of monster is
capable of such inhumanity?

19:36.981 --> 19:38.380
I can think of one.

19:39.350 --> 19:40.817
Oh, as can I.

19:57.802 --> 19:59.435
(CULLEN GRUNTING)

20:08.679 --> 20:10.011
(GRUNTING)

20:19.790 --> 20:21.189
(GRUNTING)

20:25.863 --> 20:30.466
(STUTTERING) Untie me, Mr. Bohannon.
I can help you.

20:31.034 --> 20:32.401
Devil!

20:32.970 --> 20:34.637
- Mr. Bohannon...
- (GROANS)

20:40.077 --> 20:41.243
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

20:41.679 --> 20:43.178
What, huh?

20:43.647 --> 20:45.080
It's just a snake.

20:46.650 --> 20:47.816
(WHIMPERING)

20:51.121 --> 20:52.320
(SHUDDERING)

20:54.258 --> 20:55.390
(GRUNTS)

21:07.037 --> 21:11.857
Trapper once told me
that squirming is a...

21:11.858 --> 21:13.842
It's a soul's way of leaving the body.

21:16.613 --> 21:18.280
Said it could last for minutes.

21:28.791 --> 21:29.957
Huh...

21:32.361 --> 21:34.195
Guess it depends on the soul.

21:36.972 --> 21:37.971
(GRUNTING)

21:44.157 --> 21:45.858
(GRUNTS)

21:50.027 --> 21:51.593
Sure you don't want none?

21:54.598 --> 21:55.880
(GROANS)

21:55.881 --> 21:59.346
You could be sharing a hot
meal with your wife and child.

22:02.006 --> 22:06.108
Instead you are out in the cold,

22:06.109 --> 22:09.195
with a festering wound.

22:11.966 --> 22:15.218
It's interesting you
would rather be here,

22:15.219 --> 22:18.539
offering me sustenance,
instead of your family.

22:21.075 --> 22:22.992
I'd rather keep 'em far away from you.

22:22.993 --> 22:25.027
If protecting them was your only motive,

22:25.028 --> 22:26.979
you would have been safer to kill me.

22:28.249 --> 22:30.049
And you fear killing me.

22:32.653 --> 22:33.886
Why?

22:35.089 --> 22:36.588
- I fear...
- Hmm.

22:37.458 --> 22:39.641
I fear it would bring you peace.

22:39.642 --> 22:41.227
Son of a bitch.

22:44.932 --> 22:46.431
And I will see you hang.

22:47.635 --> 22:50.019
If your misguided see of justice

22:50.020 --> 22:54.306
requires that I hang for my crimes,

22:55.777 --> 23:00.779
surely you can understand that
you must hang there beside me...

23:01.848 --> 23:03.181
For yours.

23:05.653 --> 23:07.753
And, the bodies you have piled up

23:09.122 --> 23:12.090
do not disappear when
you bury them away,

23:13.193 --> 23:14.693
out of sight.

23:16.863 --> 23:18.797
And you bring death everywhere.

23:24.471 --> 23:25.837
You scared?

23:35.382 --> 23:38.183
Oh... (SIGHS)

23:38.885 --> 23:41.520
You need your rest, Mr. Bohannon, hmm?

23:44.624 --> 23:46.024
Hmm,

23:47.828 --> 23:49.360
I'll rest soon enough.

23:49.762 --> 23:52.596
Well, I certainly hope
you do not mind if I do.

23:55.435 --> 23:57.401
We have a long journey ahead.

24:00.173 --> 24:01.306
(SPITS)

24:10.884 --> 24:12.851
(BIRDS TRILLING)

24:33.172 --> 24:34.705
(WHIMPERS, GROANS)

24:35.074 --> 24:36.841
(PANTING)

24:40.413 --> 24:41.712
Shit.

24:42.948 --> 24:45.282
Ah, I warned you, hmm?

24:45.585 --> 24:46.784
(TSKING)

24:52.791 --> 24:54.257
(YAWNING)

24:57.863 --> 24:58.862
(GRUNTS)

25:02.701 --> 25:06.853
Mmm, wasting precious
resources could prove fatal.

25:06.854 --> 25:08.638
(HEAVY BREATHING)

25:10.141 --> 25:13.342
- Yeah, I got plenty of water.
- I was referring to the bullets.

25:34.865 --> 25:36.064
(RELOADS GUN)

25:53.984 --> 25:55.634
(BREATHING SHARPLY)

25:55.635 --> 25:57.419
(SCREAMING IN AGONY)

25:58.188 --> 25:59.771
(GROANING)

25:59.772 --> 26:01.490
(MOANING)

26:05.262 --> 26:06.828
(HEAVY BREATHING)

26:14.883 --> 26:16.750
Down into the desert, then?

26:27.515 --> 26:28.849
(CULLEN BREATHING SHARPLY)

26:29.538 --> 26:30.870
(CULLEN GROANS)

26:53.121 --> 26:55.021
(GRUNTING)

27:03.398 --> 27:04.497
(GROANS)

27:05.834 --> 27:07.400
(HEAVY BREATHING)

27:11.039 --> 27:12.172
(COUGHING)

27:18.913 --> 27:20.213
(SIGHS)

27:21.483 --> 27:23.049
(GRUNTING)

27:26.021 --> 27:28.038
Right there is Camp Douglas.

27:28.039 --> 27:29.222
- Hmm?
- (GRUNTS)

27:32.093 --> 27:35.027
Exactly 40 miles

27:35.730 --> 27:37.363
west of Gobbler's Knob.

27:42.904 --> 27:44.136
Ride.

27:44.939 --> 27:46.071
Move.

27:48.743 --> 27:50.376
I said ride.

27:52.246 --> 27:53.529
Get back up on that horse.

27:53.530 --> 27:55.665
We were not meant to settle
this inside a courtroom.

27:55.666 --> 27:57.700
We will settle this as God...

27:57.701 --> 27:59.234
As God planned.

27:59.235 --> 28:00.520
Here in the desert.

28:00.755 --> 28:02.171
I said get back up on the horse.

28:02.172 --> 28:04.774
You want final judgment upon me,

28:04.775 --> 28:06.675
you will have to hand it down yourself,

28:06.676 --> 28:09.261
as I most certainly intend to do.

28:10.664 --> 28:12.864
- I ain't your judge.
- Yes, you are.

28:13.334 --> 28:15.934
You are the only one who knows
me, same as I know you!

28:16.404 --> 28:19.138
Do you think the world stops
when you leave it behind?

28:19.940 --> 28:21.022
Does it stop for...

28:21.023 --> 28:24.126
For Mary and... And Joshua
when you left for war?

28:24.127 --> 28:28.397
Does it stop for Naomi
when you abandoned her...

28:28.398 --> 28:30.165
- And William?
- Get on the horse.

28:30.166 --> 28:32.134
You cannot see it, can you?

28:32.135 --> 28:33.469
It is right there in front of you

28:33.470 --> 28:37.172
but your myopic single-mindedness
on prosecuting me

28:37.173 --> 28:39.208
has blinded you to the simple facts!

28:39.209 --> 28:41.693
- I ain't asking you again.
- You like this!

28:42.363 --> 28:44.979
You would rather be on death's door

28:44.980 --> 28:47.281
than with Naomi and William.

28:47.282 --> 28:50.668
No, death and killing have
been your only wives.

28:51.371 --> 28:53.003
Your only family.

28:54.774 --> 28:56.307
- (GROANS)
- (HORSE WHINNYING)

